<p>homes where our Madam treated us very well gave us clean extra straw &amp; table, boxes to sit on &amp; books to read. Slept OK you bet, quite at home.</p>
<p>19th &ndash; Wednesday.<br/>Drill as usual arranged. Paid later on. many shops here &amp; lived well.</p>
<p>20th. Thursday<br/>Physical jerks. Packed up &amp; Moved off at 9am. for Warloy about 9 miles. Big E.F. Canteen handy &amp; big billets. living well.</p>
<p>21st. Friday.<br/>Parades till noon.</p>
<p>Moving orders at 1 to set off at 1.30 &amp; thought it was for the trenches . After marching for 1 hour halted &amp; were told t'was</p>
